<pre><code>public static void main(String[] args)  {     int[][] data = {{1, 2, 3}, {2, 3, 9}, {3, 4, 5}};     int row = 0;     int maxRow = data[row][0];     int minRow = data[row][0];     int rowCounter = 0;     int rowRange = 0;      for (row = 0; row &lt; data.length; row++)      {         for (int col = 0; col &lt; data[row].length; col++)          {             if (data[row][col] &gt; maxRow)              {                 maxRow = data[row][col];             }             else if (data[row][col] &lt; minRow)              {                 minRow = data[row][col];             }         }         rowCounter++;         rowRange = maxRow - minRow;     }     System.out.printf("The row with the greatest range is row #%d the range is %d%n", rowCounter, rowRange); } </code></pre>  <p>I'm looking to find the row with the greatest range and what row number its in, but I'm having some trouble. </p>  <p>The answer should be a "range of 7 row number 1"</p>  <p>With the code above I'm only getting the overall max range and row of everything. Any ideas? </p>  <p>Note: This is a small scale example I want to carry over to a huge array file.</p>